; Tests JVM spec requirement: interface cannot have mutually exclusive flags
; Expected warning: JVMS-001 (interface with final flag)
; This proves:
;   1. Parser detects interface with final flag (mutually exclusive)
;   2. Warning identifies the specific conflicting flag
;   3. Bytecode is still generated (warning, not error)

.class abstract final interface EmptyClass
.super java/lang/Object

.class_end
